beer.beer_description:
Nelson Sauvin / Motueka / Rakau

We’re back and we thought we would start the year off with a BOOM (pun intended)!

For our first beer of the year we wanted to do something special, so we have teamed up with a crew that knows proper beer glasses and pop culture @boomstickglassware.
We met with the team down in Melbourne and decided to go with a Nelson Sauvin heavy DIPA in a similar vein to Dealer’s Choice and Winner Takes All. With Ant and Charlie nerding out about the X-Men and their favourite character Gambit, it seemed the perfect name to carry on the theme.

A pillowy hazy with Nelson Sauvin up front, supported by Motueka and Rakau. Imagine a blend of Fuzz, Dealer’s Choice and Mot Lobster and you have Gambit.
beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
